1
00:00:07,033 --> 00:00:11,233
笙ｪI've braved the storms, walked through the rain笙ｪ

2
00:00:11,267 --> 00:00:14,633
笙ｪSeen the highs and lows along the way笙ｪ

3
00:00:14,833 --> 00:00:18,033
笙ｪBut you stay quiet, never change笙ｪ

4
00:00:18,233 --> 00:00:21,633
笙ｪLike a child who dreams beneath the stars笙ｪ

5
00:00:21,700 --> 00:00:25,033
笙ｪI've read the story in your eyes笙ｪ

6
00:00:25,267 --> 00:00:28,533
笙ｪAnd finally, nothing's left to hide笙ｪ

7
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:32,133
笙ｪYou won't give in to a world so cold笙ｪ

8
00:00:32,267 --> 00:00:35,733
笙ｪSo you wander through it on your own笙ｪ

9
00:00:35,867 --> 00:00:39,333
笙ｪMaybe fate has drawn us near笙ｪ

10
00:00:39,433 --> 00:00:42,333
笙ｪJust to help you learn to believe笙ｪ

11
00:00:42,567 --> 00:00:45,500
笙ｪEverything you've questioned deep inside笙ｪ

12
00:00:45,633 --> 00:00:49,733
笙ｪI'll be the proof you need笙ｪ

13
00:00:49,867 --> 00:00:51,167
笙ｪI've made my choice笙ｪ

14
00:00:51,267 --> 00:00:54,133
笙ｪFor you, I'll be brave and break the rules笙ｪ

15
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:57,367
笙ｪWhat's there to fear even if the world is right and I am wrong?笙ｪ

16
00:00:58,067 --> 00:01:00,933
笙ｪOne day, all of this will turn into memories笙ｪ

17
00:01:01,467 --> 00:01:04,367
笙ｪEvery storm we faced will turn into our life's scenery笙ｪ

18
00:01:05,133 --> 00:01:08,033
笙ｪFor you, I'll be brave and break the rules笙ｪ

19
00:01:08,333 --> 00:01:11,267
笙ｪWhat's there to fear even if the world is right and I am wrong?笙ｪ

20
00:01:11,967 --> 00:01:14,833
笙ｪEven if, in the end, the whole world turns against me笙ｪ

21
00:01:15,333 --> 00:01:18,267
笙ｪI won't regret having loved you笙ｪ

22
00:01:18,367 --> 00:01:21,933
笙ｪWith all my heart笙ｪ

23
00:01:22,167 --> 00:01:25,767
笙ｪI've held you close笙ｪ

24
00:01:25,867 --> 00:01:29,467
笙ｪWalked by your side笙ｪ

25
00:01:29,633 --> 00:01:33,933
笙ｪAnd loved the fire that burned inside you笙ｪ

26
00:01:33,933 --> 00:01:35,467
[The First Frost]

27
00:01:35,467 --> 00:01:36,967
[Adapted from the novel of the same name by Zhu Yi on www.jjwxc.net]

28
00:01:38,367 --> 00:01:38,933
Wen Yifan

29
00:01:41,267 --> 00:01:42,467
am I just your backup option?

30
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:15,667
Goodbye.

31
00:02:17,633 --> 00:02:18,300
Goodbye.

32
00:02:47,033 --> 00:02:51,700
[Episode 1]
[Goodbye, Sang Yan]

33
00:02:59,567 --> 00:03:03,067
[News Interview Van, Nanwu TV's First News Team; Six Years Later]

34
00:03:07,033 --> 00:03:08,067
They are chasing too closely.

35
00:03:09,233 --> 00:03:10,300
It's fine. Keep steady.

36
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:14,167
How do we go?

37
00:03:16,133 --> 00:03:16,700
Turn left!

38
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:30,700
Be careful!

39
00:03:46,367 --> 00:03:47,467
You're running pretty fast, huh?

40
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,133
- Run again? - You want to race me?

41
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:50,033
Get down!

42
00:03:50,533 --> 00:03:51,400
- Hurry up and open the door! - Open it!

43
00:03:52,267 --> 00:03:53,200
Open it. Don't you hear me?

44
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:53,833
Get down!

45
00:03:54,267 --> 00:03:55,233
Hurry up!

46
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:56,433
Low it.

47
00:03:56,433 --> 00:03:57,433
Lower the window!

48
00:03:58,200 --> 00:03:59,433
- I'm lowering it, sir. - You're racing me, huh?

49
00:03:59,700 --> 00:04:00,400
Where's the stuff?

50
00:04:00,633 --> 00:04:01,267
It's on the back seat!

51
00:04:08,467 --> 00:04:09,800
Nanwu TV, huh?

52
00:04:10,167 --> 00:04:11,267
I'll remember you.

53
00:04:11,700 --> 00:04:13,367
Don't make me smash your TV station!

54
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:24,433
What should we do, Yifan?

55
00:04:25,867 --> 00:04:26,867
Safety comes first.

56
00:04:28,867 --> 00:04:29,567
Wen Yifan

57
00:04:29,867 --> 00:04:31,867
I don't care how well you did at Yihe Daily

58
00:04:31,867 --> 00:04:33,633
that traditional paper media.

59
00:04:33,933 --> 00:04:35,233
But if you can't adjust to the work here

60
00:04:35,433 --> 00:04:36,067
I'm sorry

61
00:04:36,133 --> 00:04:37,367
you'll be eliminated

62
00:04:37,467 --> 00:04:38,567
once the probation period's over.

63
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:41,633
What's that sound?

64
00:04:43,733 --> 00:04:44,300
Get out of the car.

65
00:04:52,933 --> 00:04:53,733
- Call an ambulance. - Yifan

66
00:04:53,733 --> 00:04:55,400
should I use my phone to get some material first?

67
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:57,000
What's more important, saving lives or reporting?

68
00:04:58,633 --> 00:04:59,133
Hello.

69
00:05:00,167 --> 00:05:01,133
We've had a car accident here.

70
00:05:01,267 --> 00:05:03,267
I'm in the Binjiang District...

71
00:05:03,833 --> 00:05:04,500
Hongguang Avenue...

72
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:05,733
Yes!

73
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:07,400
Please come quickly.

74
00:05:08,433 --> 00:05:09,033
Wait a second.

75
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:10,500
Come on.

76
00:05:14,267 --> 00:05:14,767
Give me your hand!

77
00:05:15,933 --> 00:05:17,367
- Help! - Be careful.

78
00:05:17,367 --> 00:05:18,733
- Take care. - Don't let go!

79
00:05:19,167 --> 00:05:19,933
We're done for!

80
00:05:23,033 --> 00:05:23,667
Be careful!

81
00:05:25,667 --> 00:05:26,567
Thank you!

82
00:05:57,733 --> 00:05:58,500
What are you doing?

83
00:05:59,033 --> 00:06:00,067
What's wrong?

84
00:06:00,067 --> 00:06:01,400
I'm doing laundry.

85
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:03,200
I didn't plan on mixing my clothes with yours

86
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:04,300
so I washed them first this time.

87
00:06:04,300 --> 00:06:06,500
And don't think I'm afraid of you, alright?

88
00:06:06,500 --> 00:06:08,333
Always complaining to the landlord.

89
00:06:08,733 --> 00:06:09,733
I'm not buying into that!

90
00:06:24,433 --> 00:06:25,033
Let go!

91
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:51,067
Hello, Qiao.

92
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:53,767
You finally picked up the phone!

93
00:06:53,833 --> 00:06:55,867
Do you know who I just ran into?

94
00:06:55,867 --> 00:06:58,433
I ran into my high school deskmate

95
00:06:58,733 --> 00:07:00,733
the really handsome vice monitor.

96
00:07:00,733 --> 00:07:02,367
The key point is

97
00:07:02,567 --> 00:07:04,267
I'm a mess with my hair all over.

98
00:07:04,267 --> 00:07:05,400
From morning till now

99
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:06,867
I've taken ten orders already.

100
00:07:06,867 --> 00:07:08,100
I'm in such a bad state.

101
00:07:08,233 --> 00:07:09,667
It's so embarrassing.

102
00:07:09,667 --> 00:07:11,000
Don't worry too much.

103
00:07:11,667 --> 00:07:12,867
What's up? Why'd you call?

104
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:15,000
How about we go out tonight and have some fun?

105
00:07:15,433 --> 00:07:16,600
Reporter Wen

106
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:18,500
you've been working overtime for a whole week.

107
00:07:18,767 --> 00:07:19,800
If you don't take a break

108
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:20,733
I'm afraid you'll collapse.

109
00:07:21,067 --> 00:07:22,033
My friend said

110
00:07:22,033 --> 00:07:23,767
a new restaurant bar just opened on Gastropub Street.

111
00:07:24,033 --> 00:07:25,600
The boss is super handsome.

112
00:07:27,133 --> 00:07:28,367
Why do I hear water running over there?

113
00:07:28,367 --> 00:07:29,200
Are you doing the dishes?

114
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:30,933
Washing up.

115
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:32,533
Did you just wake up?

116
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:35,433
It's already 2 p.m.

117
00:07:35,433 --> 00:07:36,600
What were you doing last night?

118
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:37,433
I couldn't sleep.

119
00:07:37,733 --> 00:07:39,467
Oh, let me take you to check out some men.

120
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:40,400
Handsome

121
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:41,133
fresh

122
00:07:41,767 --> 00:07:43,000
hot, and steamy

123
00:07:43,233 --> 00:07:44,133
men.

124
00:07:44,267 --> 00:07:45,467
I don't have the energy to check out men.

125
00:07:46,233 --> 00:07:47,200
Just one quick glance.

126
00:07:47,767 --> 00:07:48,733
Alright, it's a deal then.

127
00:07:49,033 --> 00:07:50,067
Let's not miss it tonight.

128
00:07:50,233 --> 00:07:50,833
Bye.

129
00:08:06,300 --> 00:08:07,033
Are you sure

130
00:08:07,367 --> 00:08:08,567
there is a restaurant bar here?

131
00:08:09,067 --> 00:08:10,233
I pass by here every day after work

132
00:08:10,233 --> 00:08:11,533
but I've never seen it.

133
00:08:16,367 --> 00:08:16,933
Lately

134
00:08:16,933 --> 00:08:19,000
everyone likes to hang out here

135
00:08:19,567 --> 00:08:20,200
relaxing

136
00:08:20,367 --> 00:08:21,200
chilling out

137
00:08:21,267 --> 00:08:21,867
and living slowly.

138
00:08:24,567 --> 00:08:26,767
No wonder this place is called Gastropub Street.

139
00:08:28,033 --> 00:08:29,433
Look, it's over there.

140
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:31,167
It's called "Overtime"?

141
00:08:32,167 --> 00:08:33,233
How boring.

142
00:08:34,233 --> 00:08:36,667
What a nice and thoughtful name!

143
00:08:36,667 --> 00:08:38,400
It's basically a safe haven for office workers.

144
00:08:38,767 --> 00:08:39,800
Imagine it, when your boss

145
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:41,233
[Overtime]
calls and asks where you are at night

146
00:08:41,233 --> 00:08:42,667
you can just tell them you're at Overtime.

147
00:08:44,833 --> 00:08:45,633
Is it newly opened?

148
00:08:45,633 --> 00:08:46,200
Right.

149
00:08:46,567 --> 00:08:47,833
No wonder I haven't noticed it before.

150
00:08:48,367 --> 00:08:49,033
Let's go.

151
00:09:05,633 --> 00:09:06,267
Take a look!

152
00:09:15,833 --> 00:09:16,467
Let's go inside.

153
00:09:16,900 --> 00:09:17,400
Okay.

154
00:09:27,867 --> 00:09:30,867
It really is a paradise for overtime workers.

155
00:09:37,500 --> 00:09:38,900
Is the boss absent?

156
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:40,800
Hello, misses

157
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:42,000
what can we get for you two?

158
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:43,133
No need

159
00:09:43,167 --> 00:09:44,067
we'll take care of it ourselves.

160
00:09:44,167 --> 00:09:44,667
Okay.

161
00:09:44,767 --> 00:09:46,433
If you ever need anything, just scan to order.

162
00:09:46,433 --> 00:09:47,000
Alright.

163
00:09:48,667 --> 00:09:51,467
Could the boss be that waiter from earlier?

164
00:09:51,567 --> 00:09:52,567
No way.

165
00:09:52,900 --> 00:09:53,800
The boss here

166
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:56,433
is basically the headliner of Gastropub Street.

167
00:10:01,467 --> 00:10:02,400
The person next to him?

168
00:10:03,367 --> 00:10:04,233
Probably not.

169
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:17,767
Oh, right

170
00:10:18,400 --> 00:10:19,433
didn't I tell you earlier

171
00:10:19,433 --> 00:10:21,133
that I ran into a guy on the road?

172
00:10:21,733 --> 00:10:23,633
He's the vice monitor from our first year of high school.

173
00:10:23,833 --> 00:10:26,167
I heard he also went to Nanwu University

174
00:10:27,033 --> 00:10:28,833
and he was in the same class

175
00:10:28,833 --> 00:10:29,900
as your classmate, Sang Yan.

176
00:10:30,167 --> 00:10:31,967
But I haven't really seen him since.

177
00:10:33,067 --> 00:10:34,500
Speaking of which, do you remember Sang...?

178
00:10:40,567 --> 00:10:41,133
Look!

179
00:10:41,500 --> 00:10:42,967
Is that the boss of the restaurant bar?

180
00:10:42,967 --> 00:10:43,900
I haven't finished ordering yet.

181
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:44,800
Come over and take a look!

182
00:10:45,500 --> 00:10:46,000
Look.

183
00:10:46,867 --> 00:10:47,600
Is it him?

184
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:50,733
Quick, take a look.

185
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:52,767
That handsome figure from behind.

186
00:10:52,900 --> 00:10:53,967
How could it be him?

187
00:10:58,500 --> 00:10:59,633
Enough, stop staring.

188
00:11:01,433 --> 00:11:02,233
Sorry!

189
00:11:02,967 --> 00:11:04,067
How could you be so careless?

190
00:11:04,067 --> 00:11:04,867
It's fine.

191
00:11:05,267 --> 00:11:06,567
I'll go to the restroom to clean it up.

192
00:11:06,567 --> 00:11:07,733
It could be washed off, right?

193
00:11:08,033 --> 00:11:09,000
I'm so sorry.

194
00:11:10,067 --> 00:11:10,900
Sorry.

195
00:11:10,900 --> 00:11:11,767
It's okay.

196
00:11:27,667 --> 00:11:31,433
笙ｪThe dust of lies and your wounds笙ｪ

197
00:11:31,533 --> 00:11:34,867
笙ｪAll hide in your eyes笙ｪ

198
00:11:35,467 --> 00:11:40,633
笙ｪDon't wander off in your dreams笙ｪ

199
00:11:42,267 --> 00:11:47,733
笙ｪMy dear, don't say goodbye笙ｪ

200
00:11:49,300 --> 00:11:53,067
笙ｪCan you hold me in your freezing night?笙ｪ

201
00:11:53,767 --> 00:11:56,167
笙ｪDon't you ever hide笙ｪ

202
00:11:56,367 --> 00:11:58,300
笙ｪThis time?笙ｪ

203
00:12:05,167 --> 00:12:06,467
I saw you earlier.

204
00:12:24,900 --> 00:12:25,433
Change into it.

205
00:12:26,433 --> 00:12:27,400
I'm the boss here.

206
00:12:27,833 --> 00:12:28,500
My surname is Sang.

207
00:12:29,033 --> 00:12:30,200
He doesn't recognize me...

208
00:12:30,467 --> 00:12:32,000
I'm sorry, due to our mistake

209
00:12:32,333 --> 00:12:34,067
we caused you trouble and inconvenience.

210
00:12:34,167 --> 00:12:35,667
If you ever need anything, feel free to tell me.

211
00:12:35,867 --> 00:12:36,500
Also

212
00:12:36,733 --> 00:12:38,733
all of your consumption tonight

213
00:12:38,733 --> 00:12:39,500
is on the house.

214
00:12:40,433 --> 00:12:42,000
I hope it doesn't ruin your good mood.

215
00:12:42,467 --> 00:12:43,867
Looks like he really doesn't recognize me.

216
00:12:43,900 --> 00:12:45,367
No need, it's okay.

217
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:46,667
Then I'll take my leave.

218
00:12:47,367 --> 00:12:48,000
Sang...

219
00:12:53,467 --> 00:12:54,800
Well, I should pretend not to know him.

220
00:12:55,833 --> 00:12:56,667
The Headliner...

221
00:12:57,900 --> 00:12:58,800
Your coat.

222
00:13:00,333 --> 00:13:01,400
Sang...

223
00:13:02,167 --> 00:13:03,267
The Headliner?

224
00:13:07,167 --> 00:13:07,733
Sorry

225
00:13:08,567 --> 00:13:10,433
we are a proper restaurant bar here.

226
00:13:11,767 --> 00:13:12,967
That's quite a shame.

227
00:13:14,367 --> 00:13:16,267
Aren't you happy wearing my clothes?

228
00:13:16,800 --> 00:13:18,400
Seems like I'm more famous than Overtime.

229
00:13:19,333 --> 00:13:20,600
Take it as a souvenir.

230
00:13:36,667 --> 00:13:37,267
You're back.

231
00:13:40,367 --> 00:13:42,433
I just met the boss in the restroom.

232
00:13:42,667 --> 00:13:43,333
He said...

233
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:47,033
He really said that?

234
00:13:48,467 --> 00:13:49,567
Why didn't he advise you

235
00:13:49,567 --> 00:13:51,200
to frame it at your house?

236
00:13:51,833 --> 00:13:53,000
That's exactly what he meant.

237
00:13:54,567 --> 00:13:56,067
But don't mind what he said.

238
00:13:56,067 --> 00:13:57,167
Handsome, we need to order.

239
00:13:57,167 --> 00:13:58,267
After all, he's the star attraction here.

240
00:13:58,667 --> 00:13:59,467
Let me take a good look at him.

241
00:13:59,800 --> 00:14:02,233
- Really? - Of course.

242
00:14:02,333 --> 00:14:04,133
Handsome, we need to order here.

243
00:14:04,833 --> 00:14:05,500
What do you need?

244
00:14:05,633 --> 00:14:06,667
Alright.

245
00:14:06,667 --> 00:14:08,067
Why is there someone next to him?

246
00:14:08,467 --> 00:14:09,433
He's got such good luck with ladies.

247
00:14:12,733 --> 00:14:14,367
Hello, here's your drink.

248
00:14:14,367 --> 00:14:15,800
And here's your refund.

249
00:14:16,067 --> 00:14:16,900
What's this about?

250
00:14:17,733 --> 00:14:19,733
Sorry, it was my mistake earlier.

251
00:14:19,733 --> 00:14:21,033
The boss said

252
00:14:21,067 --> 00:14:22,200
that this table's on the house.

253
00:14:22,467 --> 00:14:23,567
It's not that serious.

254
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:24,600
Take the money back.

255
00:14:24,733 --> 00:14:25,233
It's okay.

256
00:14:25,233 --> 00:14:26,800
It's common for men to buy drinks for pretty ladies.

257
00:14:28,167 --> 00:14:28,867
Thank you.

258
00:14:36,633 --> 00:14:37,333
Where's the boss?

259
00:14:41,633 --> 00:14:42,467
Give me a drink.

260
00:14:58,733 --> 00:14:59,267
She didn't accept it?

261
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:00,900
Sir

262
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:03,167
this might not be the money for the drink.

263
00:15:03,567 --> 00:15:05,833
I just heard those two customers saying...

264
00:15:06,567 --> 00:15:08,067
You've forgotten why you came here?

265
00:15:08,900 --> 00:15:09,967
How could a simple "look"

266
00:15:10,133 --> 00:15:12,167
do justice to his elegance?

267
00:15:14,900 --> 00:15:17,367
This could be something for you...

268
00:15:18,433 --> 00:15:19,167
What thing?

269
00:15:19,900 --> 00:15:20,633
A tip.

270
00:15:23,767 --> 00:15:24,900
Sir, are you accepting it?

271
00:15:26,867 --> 00:15:27,833
I'll go get busy now.

272
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:30,200
Sir

273
00:15:30,367 --> 00:15:31,233
what's going on?

274
00:15:31,867 --> 00:15:33,400
Our bar's not that desperate yet, are we?

275
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:35,167
You're really going the extra mile.

276
00:15:57,367 --> 00:15:58,067
Yifan

277
00:15:58,233 --> 00:15:59,367
how's the house I found for you?

278
00:15:59,367 --> 00:16:00,433
Are you settling in alright?

279
00:16:01,033 --> 00:16:03,200
Although the environment isn't that great

280
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:05,233
at least it's convenient for transportation.

281
00:16:05,233 --> 00:16:06,900
This should make your commute a bit easier.

282
00:16:07,500 --> 00:16:09,233
If I hadn't chosen to separate from him

283
00:16:10,567 --> 00:16:12,167
back in high school

284
00:16:13,233 --> 00:16:14,867
what would I be like now?

285
00:16:17,233 --> 00:16:18,600
Would I be happier than now?

286
00:16:19,267 --> 00:16:20,667
And braver?

287
00:16:22,733 --> 00:16:24,033
In this world

288
00:16:24,633 --> 00:16:26,200
is there really another me?

289
00:16:29,800 --> 00:16:31,333
In a parallel universe

290
00:16:32,433 --> 00:16:34,800
she might walk a completely different path than mine.

291
00:16:37,133 --> 00:16:38,667
If we met at this moment

292
00:16:40,467 --> 00:16:41,367
I wonder

293
00:16:41,967 --> 00:16:43,467
how would the other me see me?

294
00:17:10,433 --> 00:17:11,000
Yifan

295
00:17:12,167 --> 00:17:13,767
are you listening?

296
00:17:14,967 --> 00:17:15,733
What did you say?

297
00:17:16,167 --> 00:17:17,800
I said, are you settling in alright

298
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:18,967
in the house I found for you?

299
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:21,800
It's fine, I guess.

300
00:17:22,867 --> 00:17:23,667
Then that's good.

301
00:17:25,867 --> 00:17:26,967
I've arrived at the station.

302
00:17:27,167 --> 00:17:28,967
Be safe and text me when you get back.

303
00:17:28,967 --> 00:17:29,600
- Alright. - Bye.

304
00:17:29,600 --> 00:17:30,400
Take care.

305
00:17:45,633 --> 00:17:49,900
笙ｪOnce again, I hear the farewell from that day笙ｪ

306
00:17:52,467 --> 00:17:57,267
笙ｪTears fall as the memory replays笙ｪ

307
00:17:59,233 --> 00:18:04,367
笙ｪLetting go of the past I once held tight笙ｪ

308
00:18:05,467 --> 00:18:07,067
笙ｪWishing for笙ｪ

309
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:09,933
笙ｪA better chapter ahead笙ｪ

310
00:18:11,933 --> 00:18:15,933
笙ｪThe answers of time笙ｪ

311
00:18:16,667 --> 00:18:19,433
笙ｪShould be handed in a bit late笙ｪ

312
00:18:19,967 --> 00:18:26,500
笙ｪThe journey ahead should keep extending笙ｪ

313
00:18:29,100 --> 00:18:34,333
笙ｪI fear you might be a little late笙ｪ

314
00:18:36,067 --> 00:18:41,500
笙ｪLeaving me lost in the crowd笙ｪ

315
00:18:42,467 --> 00:18:46,233
笙ｪBefore we met笙ｪ

316
00:18:46,833 --> 00:18:49,233
笙ｪEvery long night was meaningless笙ｪ

317
00:18:50,333 --> 00:18:55,500
笙ｪSearching for you is destined to be a painful journey...笙ｪ

318
00:18:59,367 --> 00:19:00,667
You're back so late.

319
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:02,867
I'm not washing my clothes with yours today.

320
00:19:02,867 --> 00:19:04,033
I've washed them first.

321
00:19:04,233 --> 00:19:05,567
You're back. Join our meal?

322
00:19:05,733 --> 00:19:06,400
No, thanks.

323
00:19:07,167 --> 00:19:08,833
Come on, Yifan, come eat with us.

324
00:19:09,300 --> 00:19:10,500
No, thanks.

325
00:19:15,867 --> 00:19:16,733
Sir

326
00:19:17,033 --> 00:19:18,633
can you stop acting like this all the time?

327
00:19:18,833 --> 00:19:19,967
When my wife did the laundry in the summer

328
00:19:19,967 --> 00:19:21,033
you threw your clothes in there too.

329
00:19:21,033 --> 00:19:21,933
Isn't that disgusting?

330
00:19:22,067 --> 00:19:23,267
What about the risk of infection?

331
00:19:23,267 --> 00:19:24,433
What infection?

332
00:19:24,433 --> 00:19:25,300
I'm pure clean!

333
00:19:25,300 --> 00:19:26,467
I shower every two days!

334
00:19:26,767 --> 00:19:28,667
You've got a skin condition and athlete's foot!

335
00:19:28,667 --> 00:19:29,767
I'm very clean!

336
00:19:29,767 --> 00:19:30,833
I'm telling you

337
00:19:30,833 --> 00:19:31,767
I'm warning you

338
00:19:31,767 --> 00:19:32,833
don't act like this again!

339
00:19:37,967 --> 00:19:43,367
笙ｪMaybe forgetting some expectations笙ｪ

340
00:19:44,100 --> 00:19:45,233
笙ｪWould笙ｪ

341
00:19:46,233 --> 00:19:51,733
笙ｪBring me surprise笙ｪ

342
00:20:06,867 --> 00:20:07,367
Lady

343
00:20:07,833 --> 00:20:08,467
what would you like to drink?

344
00:20:11,933 --> 00:20:13,667
When we came here for dinner last night

345
00:20:13,667 --> 00:20:14,500
We dropped a bracelet.

346
00:20:14,667 --> 00:20:15,433
Did anyone find it?

347
00:20:15,900 --> 00:20:17,067
Bracelet?

348
00:20:19,867 --> 00:20:20,767
Last night

349
00:20:21,300 --> 00:20:22,467
which table were you sitting at?

350
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:24,067
That one.

351
00:20:24,733 --> 00:20:25,400
The first table.

352
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:26,633
These past two days

353
00:20:26,633 --> 00:20:28,000
I've been checking lost items.

354
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:29,200
I really haven't seen a bracelet.

355
00:20:29,633 --> 00:20:30,267
Zhuo

356
00:20:30,467 --> 00:20:31,200
come over here.

357
00:20:31,567 --> 00:20:33,233
This lady was sitting at that table last night.

358
00:20:33,500 --> 00:20:34,633
Did you see a bracelet dropped there?

359
00:20:36,800 --> 00:20:38,200
I accidentally bumped into you that day.

360
00:20:38,300 --> 00:20:39,067
Sorry.

361
00:20:39,300 --> 00:20:40,567
Mr. Yan cleaned the place last night.

362
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:42,567
When he took the clothes

363
00:20:42,567 --> 00:20:44,200
he probably took the bracelet, too.

364
00:20:47,267 --> 00:20:47,967
It's okay.

365
00:20:47,967 --> 00:20:49,267
I'll leave my contact information.

366
00:20:49,567 --> 00:20:50,333
Okay.

367
00:20:51,067 --> 00:20:51,633
[Overtime]

368
00:20:51,633 --> 00:20:53,300
You can write it down here.

369
00:20:58,033 --> 00:20:59,200
I'm the bartender here.

370
00:20:59,200 --> 00:20:59,833
My name's He Mingbo.

371
00:21:00,233 --> 00:21:01,567
If there are any further questions

372
00:21:01,567 --> 00:21:02,600
you can contact me anytime.

373
00:21:02,733 --> 00:21:03,967
Please contact this number if it's found...

374
00:21:10,467 --> 00:21:11,233
Not giving up

375
00:21:12,033 --> 00:21:13,667
even came specifically to leave contact info?

376
00:21:16,100 --> 00:21:16,800
Sir

377
00:21:16,800 --> 00:21:18,400
she dropped a bracelet last night.

378
00:21:18,400 --> 00:21:19,267
Well, go find it.

379
00:21:19,600 --> 00:21:21,000
Don't let the customer think we're slacking off.

380
00:21:21,033 --> 00:21:21,633
Sir

381
00:21:21,867 --> 00:21:23,233
I check lost items every day.

382
00:21:23,233 --> 00:21:23,933
No bracelet.

383
00:21:25,733 --> 00:21:27,567
Are you sure there is no bracelet?

384
00:21:28,167 --> 00:21:29,100
That's impossible.

385
00:21:29,100 --> 00:21:30,067
What are you talking about?

386
00:21:30,067 --> 00:21:31,200
I check every day.

387
00:21:31,933 --> 00:21:32,667
No way.

388
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:35,033
It couldn't be there.

389
00:21:45,700 --> 00:21:46,200
Oh...

390
00:21:47,433 --> 00:21:48,100
It's found.

391
00:21:48,733 --> 00:21:49,600
Is this yours?

392
00:21:54,367 --> 00:21:54,867
Thanks.

393
00:21:54,900 --> 00:21:55,500
You're welcome.

394
00:22:02,033 --> 00:22:03,167
Didn't you check there earlier

395
00:22:03,167 --> 00:22:04,067
and find no bracelet?

396
00:22:04,067 --> 00:22:04,967
Yes.

397
00:22:21,300 --> 00:22:22,267
The bracelet has been found?

398
00:22:22,800 --> 00:22:23,867
Thanks so much!

399
00:22:24,200 --> 00:22:25,667
That bracelet was a gift from someone I like.

400
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:27,433
I'll come by another day to pick it up.

401
00:22:27,733 --> 00:22:28,833
I'm going to deliver the food first.

402
00:22:28,833 --> 00:22:29,800
Love you, Yifan.

403
00:22:43,633 --> 00:22:44,467
Do you want something?

404
00:22:44,467 --> 00:22:45,667
I'm going out to get some late-night snacks.

405
00:22:46,167 --> 00:22:47,300
No, thanks.

406
00:22:47,833 --> 00:22:48,500
Alright, we're off.

407
00:23:43,233 --> 00:23:44,967
- You didn't expect it was me, huh? - Let go of me!

408
00:23:45,467 --> 00:23:47,433
- Screaming your lungs out won't do any good! - Let go of me!

409
00:23:47,467 --> 00:23:49,633
My wife won't be back for another two hours!

410
00:23:49,867 --> 00:23:51,100
- Let go! - Just stay calm

411
00:23:51,100 --> 00:23:52,400
and give in to me!

412
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:55,833
Don't move!

413
00:23:56,233 --> 00:23:57,767
Are you sure I was just peeking?

414
00:23:58,033 --> 00:23:59,833
Are you sure I didn't install a camera?

415
00:24:01,733 --> 00:24:03,100
You're all alone.

416
00:24:03,433 --> 00:24:04,633
No one will care

417
00:24:04,633 --> 00:24:06,000
what happens to you!

418
00:24:10,400 --> 00:24:11,100
What are you doing?

419
00:24:11,267 --> 00:24:13,033
I just want to protect you!

420
00:24:14,433 --> 00:24:15,667
Look at you, all alone.

421
00:24:16,500 --> 00:24:18,167
No one's here with you for the holidays!

422
00:24:19,700 --> 00:24:20,700
Call the police!

423
00:24:27,833 --> 00:24:28,567
They hit me.

424
00:24:28,600 --> 00:24:29,667
Look at my face, covered in bruises.

425
00:24:29,767 --> 00:24:31,367
- I'm the victim here! - I was just doing the right thing.

426
00:24:31,367 --> 00:24:32,800
- Doing the right thing. - They have an affair!

427
00:24:32,800 --> 00:24:33,667
Let me tell you

428
00:24:33,667 --> 00:24:35,367
We folks from the Northeast are all good guys!

429
00:24:40,633 --> 00:24:42,267
Miss Wen, don't worry.

430
00:24:42,367 --> 00:24:43,400
Our people

431
00:24:43,400 --> 00:24:45,567
just carefully checked your place.

432
00:24:45,933 --> 00:24:46,500
We didn't find

433
00:24:46,500 --> 00:24:48,233
any cameras at the scene.

434
00:24:48,567 --> 00:24:49,933
You can go home and feel safe now.

435
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:54,667
If you're still worried

436
00:24:54,867 --> 00:24:56,167
should we send an officer

437
00:24:56,167 --> 00:24:57,200
to escort you home?

438
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:01,267
No need.

439
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:02,167
Thank you.

440
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:19,400
You're all alone.

441
00:25:19,733 --> 00:25:20,933
No one will care

442
00:25:20,933 --> 00:25:22,267
what happens to you!

443
00:25:37,067 --> 00:25:37,967
You want to sleep?

444
00:25:37,967 --> 00:25:38,467
Come

445
00:25:38,467 --> 00:25:39,867
You were just saying you wanted to sleep.

446
00:26:00,400 --> 00:26:01,567
It's not your fault.

447
00:26:04,300 --> 00:26:05,867
Take care of yourself and the kid.

448
00:26:13,033 --> 00:26:13,933
Mom

449
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:16,233
whose fault is it?

450
00:26:19,800 --> 00:26:21,067
Was it my fault?

451
00:26:32,867 --> 00:26:33,600
Yifan?

452
00:26:34,500 --> 00:26:35,233
Qiao

453
00:26:35,633 --> 00:26:36,967
Why are you here so late?

454
00:26:39,500 --> 00:26:41,367
I came to give you the bracelet.

455
00:26:41,833 --> 00:26:42,667
Come on in.

456
00:26:43,467 --> 00:26:44,233
Oh, Yifan is here.

457
00:26:44,467 --> 00:26:45,933
- Aunty. - Come on, have some fruit.

458
00:26:48,033 --> 00:26:49,100
Yifan is here!

459
00:26:49,300 --> 00:26:50,033
Yifan is here.

460
00:26:50,500 --> 00:26:51,667
- Hello! - Come in!

461
00:26:51,667 --> 00:26:52,467
Take a seat!

462
00:26:52,467 --> 00:26:53,667
Come in!

463
00:26:55,567 --> 00:26:56,400
Are you really okay?

464
00:26:59,300 --> 00:27:01,033
Can I stay here tonight?

465
00:27:02,400 --> 00:27:03,267
Of course, no problem.

466
00:27:32,833 --> 00:27:34,100
I need to leave now.

467
00:27:34,233 --> 00:27:36,200
Uncle Zheng drove me here.

468
00:27:36,200 --> 00:27:37,967
He's waiting outside.

469
00:27:37,967 --> 00:27:39,167
I can't let him wait too long.

470
00:27:39,167 --> 00:27:40,633
Call me if anything comes up.

471
00:27:40,633 --> 00:27:41,667
I'll call you back later.

472
00:27:44,933 --> 00:27:45,633
Mom

473
00:27:47,800 --> 00:27:48,667
I'm begging you.

474
00:27:50,200 --> 00:27:51,167
Please, I beg you.

475
00:27:53,800 --> 00:27:54,600
Help me.

476
00:27:54,600 --> 00:27:55,400
Do you feel okay to go home?

477
00:27:58,433 --> 00:28:00,000
Please don't leave me again.

478
00:28:13,467 --> 00:28:15,733
Little rascal, hurry up and come out.

479
00:28:15,833 --> 00:28:17,233
I can't hold it anymore.

480
00:28:17,233 --> 00:28:19,200
You've been in there for ages.

481
00:28:19,267 --> 00:28:20,967
Wushuang, Wuye, time to eat!

482
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:21,933
Coming.

483
00:28:21,933 --> 00:28:22,567
Yifan

484
00:28:22,567 --> 00:28:23,733
come out for breakfast!

485
00:28:27,667 --> 00:28:30,167
Good morning, sis.

486
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:31,667
Good morning.

487
00:28:32,067 --> 00:28:33,300
Yifan, you're awake.

488
00:28:33,567 --> 00:28:35,067
Come out for breakfast!

489
00:28:35,567 --> 00:28:37,000
Let's go, time to eat.

490
00:28:37,233 --> 00:28:37,967
Hurry. Sit here.

491
00:28:37,967 --> 00:28:38,600
Okay.

492
00:28:38,933 --> 00:28:39,500
Eat up.

493
00:28:39,833 --> 00:28:40,567
Hello, Grandpa.

494
00:28:40,567 --> 00:28:42,067
Come on, sit down.

495
00:28:42,467 --> 00:28:43,033
Little rascal

496
00:28:43,233 --> 00:28:44,067
I'm telling you

497
00:28:44,067 --> 00:28:45,100
you better come out quickly

498
00:28:45,100 --> 00:28:46,400
next time you use the bathroom.

499
00:28:46,400 --> 00:28:47,200
I know.

500
00:28:47,200 --> 00:28:48,200
Make sure you remember!

501
00:28:48,200 --> 00:28:49,367
You two, move quickly.

502
00:28:49,467 --> 00:28:50,433
Why are you sitting in my spot again?

503
00:28:50,433 --> 00:28:51,233
Go sit over there.

504
00:28:51,233 --> 00:28:51,833
Hurry up!

505
00:28:51,833 --> 00:28:52,667
Come on, Yifan.

506
00:28:52,667 --> 00:28:53,200
Help yourself

507
00:28:53,200 --> 00:28:54,000
and eat up.

508
00:28:54,400 --> 00:28:55,433
Thank you, Aunty.

509
00:28:55,433 --> 00:28:56,400
Have this lychee-flavored drink.

510
00:28:56,400 --> 00:28:57,467
It'll keep you looking young.

511
00:28:58,400 --> 00:28:59,967
- I want this one. - You want this one?

512
00:28:59,967 --> 00:29:01,367
Don't be shy. Just eat up.

513
00:29:04,100 --> 00:29:04,900
Move up a little.

514
00:29:09,867 --> 00:29:11,567
This big family is really great.

515
00:29:11,567 --> 00:29:12,367
What's so great about it?

516
00:29:12,367 --> 00:29:14,767
If you keep acting so slowly, you'll miss the dishes.

517
00:29:15,267 --> 00:29:16,733
Come over often, alright?

518
00:29:16,833 --> 00:29:18,600
I will make you breakfast every day.

519
00:29:19,100 --> 00:29:20,033
Thanks, Aunty.

520
00:29:20,367 --> 00:29:21,600
Look at you, your studies are great

521
00:29:21,600 --> 00:29:22,600
and your work is great too.

522
00:29:24,933 --> 00:29:25,467
Hello?

523
00:29:25,467 --> 00:29:26,033
Yifan

524
00:29:26,300 --> 00:29:27,767
Mr. Gan and Ms. Qian asked us

525
00:29:27,767 --> 00:29:28,867
to arrive on time today!

526
00:29:29,067 --> 00:29:29,667
I've already arrived.

527
00:29:29,667 --> 00:29:30,600
- Got it. - Hurry up!

528
00:29:35,533 --> 00:29:41,500
[Nanwu TV Station]

529
00:29:42,433 --> 00:29:43,300
She's here!

530
00:29:43,900 --> 00:29:44,600
She's here!

531
00:29:45,600 --> 00:29:46,233
What's going on?

532
00:29:46,233 --> 00:29:47,033
Why are you here so early?

533
00:29:47,033 --> 00:29:47,600
Fu Zhuang.

534
00:29:47,633 --> 00:29:48,933
Let's congratulate Yifan.

535
00:29:48,933 --> 00:29:50,367
A round of applause!

536
00:29:52,200 --> 00:29:53,267
Congratulations, Yifan!

537
00:29:53,633 --> 00:29:54,500
Congratulations, Yifan!

538
00:29:54,833 --> 00:29:55,400
Hurry!

539
00:29:55,833 --> 00:29:56,800
What's going on?

540
00:29:58,567 --> 00:29:59,167
Yifan

541
00:29:59,167 --> 00:30:01,000
This news is just like your name:

542
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:01,833
self-made

543
00:30:01,833 --> 00:30:02,667
and extraordinary.

544
00:30:03,367 --> 00:30:05,000
Today, you're the star.

545
00:30:05,000 --> 00:30:06,100
[For Doing a Good Deed]
Lin

546
00:30:06,100 --> 00:30:07,267
interview her properly later.

547
00:30:07,267 --> 00:30:08,833
- Okay. - She's the headline of today's front page.

548
00:30:08,833 --> 00:30:09,433
Alright.

549
00:30:09,933 --> 00:30:11,733
It's about the car accident days ago.

550
00:30:11,833 --> 00:30:12,633
Miss Wen Yifan

551
00:30:13,400 --> 00:30:14,633
this certificate of honor

552
00:30:14,933 --> 00:30:15,867
is to commend you

553
00:30:15,867 --> 00:30:17,167
for your actions at the car accident scene.

554
00:30:17,167 --> 00:30:18,033
You remained fearless

555
00:30:18,067 --> 00:30:19,933
and selflessly extended a helping hand.

556
00:30:20,100 --> 00:30:20,867
This is truly deserving of recognition!

557
00:30:21,267 --> 00:30:22,067
Let's give her a round of applause!

558
